Florida, which was the first to grant them to students whose
schools fail standardized tests. The state will soon be the
nation's largest voucher testing ground and is the model for a
national program proposed by Gov. George W. Bush of Texas, the
likely Republican presidential nominee. By Jodi Wilgoren.
