<P>
   TRIBUNE-NEWMEDIA (Chicago) _ Here in Chicago, the Tribune Co.
has been quietly transforming itself in recent years into what top
executives say is a new media company, which is funneling old media
content and ideas into television, cable, radio and internet
ventures. Before the deal with the Times Mirror Co., it had more
than 16 television stations, reaching more than a third of U.S.
households. There were four radio stations, an entertainment unit,
a venture capital arm, and an educational publishing unit. The
company was an early investor in America Online and Yahoo, and owns
a 25 percent stake in the WB television network and a 29 percent
stake in cable television's Food Network. By David Barboza.
