r s BC-BKN-LAKERS-NUGGETS-LA     03-14 0669
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-NUGGETS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHAQ GETS 40 AS LAKERS STREAK REACHES 19
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ There was no need for added dramatic effect, no motive
for attaching another encore to a virtuoso performance that has
already reached peak levels many times over. But Shaquille O'Neal
was not ready to retreat backstage, or to the infirmary.
</P>
<P>
   Not before another thundering crescendo and a final bow.
</P>
<P>
   So O'Neal dropped 40 points on the Denver Nuggets on Monday for
a 118-108 Lakers victory at Pepsi Center. And only afterward did
anyone let on that he was nearly held out because of a nagging
right hamstring that has apparently bothered him for a week.
</P>
<P>
   ``The big fella, he amazes me at every turn,'' said teammate
Glen Rice, who added 20 points.
</P>
<P>
   It was a timely performance too, coinciding with an equally
incredible feat: The win extended the Lakers' streak to 19 games,
third best in NBA history. They can tie the second-best mark with a
win Thursday in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   The effects of O'Neal's injury showed up in his rebounds (nine)
and blocked shots (one), but nowhere else. He scored 18 points in a
second half that he wasn't supposed to play and eight points in the
fourth quarter, in which he also made all six of his free-throw
attempts.
</P>
<P>
   He finished 14 for 20 from the field, 12 for 16 from the line
and was last seen searching for a Kinko's, because he needs to add
a new page to that MVP application.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you have a guy with a hamstring injury, and to be able to
go out there and gut it out and put up the type of performance that
he did tonight, just says a lot about how much he's grown and the
determination,'' Rice said. ``We wondered (if O'Neal would play),
and we figured that the big guy would go out there and whether it
be eight minutes or 10 minutes, he's going to give it his all. He
got it going on and it loosened up on him and he just stayed out
there and continued to play.''
</P>
<P>
   For 44 minutes, in fact. All of it was needed as the Lakers
fought back low energy (after a comeback win the night before
against Sacramento), high altitude and the uptempo, athletic
Nuggets.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers never trailed in the second half, but they never
could put the Nuggets away, either, as six Denver players scored in
double figures, led by Chris Gatling's 25 and Keon Clark's 18.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Phil Jackson said it was ``debatable whether we would
play'' O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought maybe we'd start him the first half, and the second
half just for a few minutes,'' Jackson said, ``and once he got
going, he wanted to stay and played a great game for us out there
offensively. He wasn't mobile enough to rebound and do some of the
things we like him to do defensively, but the rest of his game was
great _ assist level (seven), etc.''
</P>
<P>
   Despite all of it, and Kobe Bryant's 22 points, the Nuggets were
within five points, 107-102, with 2:30 left. But O'Neal hit four
free throws down the stretch and fed Brian Shaw on consecutive
layups, the latter a 3-point play, to make it a double-digit lead
again. Shaw finished with a season-high 14 points.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm all right,'' said O'Neal. ``I'm a little sore. Probably
take the next couple days off, stretch it, but I'm OK.''
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal, who said he's been sore since the Miami game on March 5,
said he was fine once he got warmed up. He's now averaging 42.3
points in the last four games, all with the hamstring injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``I sucked it up,'' he said. ``Cause I have heart. And I'm on a
mission.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers moved another step in that mission with their 10th
straight road win, improving their NBA-best record to 53-11.
They'll go for consecutive win No. 20 at Washington on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   All along, they've tried to ignore the streak, but they will
embrace that milestone.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'd be nice,'' Bryant said, ``because this whole season we've
achieved some things that other teams have not achieved. So it'd be
nice to have that.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
