<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   MBA-TREND _ MBA students at Emory worked with CNN to develop and
refine the Turner South concept that finally went on the air. Can
show the relation between live experiences like that and new kind
of business school graduate. With Turner, Emory voices, including
students. Can do for Wednesday. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-COM _ ITC DeltaCom has announced a deal in which the
company can use IBM to provide customers with Internet support,
including the capability of sending certified mail via the Net. The
service will be provided through e-DeltaCom, the new company
created recently by West Point-based ITC DeltaCom to focus on data
and Internet business. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WEB-HOTELSUPPLIES _ An Atlanta-based Internet site for buying
and selling hotel
</P>
<P>
   and restaurant supplies is expanding its service to reach
customers on the move. Hsupply.com, which brings together
procurement specialists and producers of consumable supplies like
tissue and soaps, is now making its service reachable by hand held
mobile devices. The service is headed by Ravi Kalakota, who has
left teaching duties at Georgia State University to devote full
time to developing the new web site. With the new wireless
capability, Kalakota said, Hsupply now allows busy executives to
approve, check the status of, and even place orders for operating
supplies instantly. The company is also developing regional
distribution points to shorten supply lines to customers. Asked if
teaching was now behind him, Kalakota, who now employes 70 people
in his Lake Hearn office, said ``let's say I have taken e-business
research to another stage, and we plan to devote the better part of
the next 10 years refining procurement sites like Hsupply.''
(Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   INCANTA _ Incanta Inc. this week announced a pact with San
Francisco-based Northpoint Communications Group, aimed at
delivering music and video services over high-speed lines. Incanta,
a six-month-old startup, will provide technology to Northpoint that
will be used over networks using digital subscriber lines _ DSL _
in 33 markets. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   PTEK _ PTEK announced Tuesday its first investment since
renaming and reshaping itself as a holding company that makes
high-tech investments. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
