<P>
   MONEYTALK - Getting slammed by a tornado, or any other natural
disaster, is bad luck. But neglecting common-sense precautions is
bad judgment. You can deal with emotional trauma later on, if big
winds or other disasters come your way. Now is the time to protect
all those financial arrangements that mean so much to your
household. (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
