<P>
   &UR; PINOCHET AND CHILE'S UNFINISHED JUSTICE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It was not quite the most miraculous recovery since Lazarus. But
when General Augusto Pinochet arose from his wheelchair to greet
his army buddies at Santiago's airport on March 3, he was sprightly
enough to embarrass two governments. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
