   &UR; Moved as BC-OLE!-JOSE-SPAIN-ECONOMIST-NYTSF &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ANGST, NOT AMBITION, GIVES EUROPEAN BANKS THE URGE TO MERGE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Deutsche Bank's planned takeover of its Frankfurt rival,
Dresdner Bank, to form the largest bank in Europe, is only the
latest in a rash of huge recent deals that have certainly made
investment-banking advisers delirious. But the truth is that the
deals have usually been defensive, done out of fear not ambition. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors...RE: Deutsche-Dresdner Bank Merger) &QL;
