<P>
   &UR; GEORGE II VS. ALBERT II: THE DANGER OF DYNASTIC POLITICS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Super Tuesday'' saw more than just the triumph of the two
establishment candidates. It saw the triumph of the ultimate
establishment: dynasticism. Political dynasties are in retreat in
most of the rest of the world. The Nehrus no longer rule India.
Britain is retiring its hereditary peers. Indonesia has kissed the
Suhartos goodbye. But in the country that was born of a revolution
against George III, the next presidential election will be fought
between two crown princes, George II and Albert II. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary, Political Editors) &QL;
</P>
