 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; AFFIRMATIVE ACTION IN FLORIDA: LOOK UNDER THE OTHER BUSH &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Inside Florida's legislature, he was praised as a visionary
reformer. Outside, he was called a ``crucifier'' and a ``bigot.''
As governor Jeb Bush delivered Florida's annual State-of-the-State
address on March 7, 1,100 angry protestors on the steps of the
Capitol in Tallahassee denounced his One Florida initiative, a plan
to end affirmative action in Florida's colleges. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Florida and Texas Editors) &QL;
</P>
