   &UR; SHOOTING OF KHATAMI FRIEND UNLOCKS IRAN'S `DUNGEON OF GHOSTS' &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TEHRAN _ Sunday morning, two men on a 1000cc motorbike shot and
critically wounded the editor-in-chief of an Iranian newspaper
which has repeatedly questioned the sinister activities of former
president Ali Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani. The victim, Saeed
Hajjarian, is a close friend and adviser of the reformist
president, Mohamed Khatami. And the motorbike? In Iran, 1000cc
motorcycles can only be used, by law, by members of the security
forces. &QL;
