 &QL; 
Sales tax out &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   New York City Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani has ended the city's
sales tax of 8.25 percent on the purchase of clothing and footwear
items costing less than $110. During the past three years the city
has held seven sales-tax-free weeks, during which New York City
retailers saw sales increase as much as 77 percent.
</P>
