<P>
   HOSPITAL INFECTIONS: Up to 2 million Americans each year
contract infections during a hospital stay, according to the
Centers for Disease Control. The infections kill almost 90,000
patients a year and cost an additional $5 billion annually to
treat. (Includes 4-column photo of a medical worker putting on
rubber gloves, 1-column photo of a woman washing hands.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TIPS BOX: How to avoid contracting an infection.
</P>
<P>
