   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SMALL-SCHOOLS (Benton Lake School District, Montana) -- Parents
of three students make the 40-mile round trip every day from the
nearest city so their children can have a slice of education's new
hottest commodity: A small school. And in Montana, the smaller the
better. By Beth Daley. 1200 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   ENVIRONMENT-SHARKS (Boston) _ Massachusetts became the nation's
leading shark-fishing state over the last decade as the cod
dwindled. Now, federal regulators say this ``trash fish,'' has been
overfished to the point of collapse. By Scott Allen. 980 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ A Gray area in California. By
Thomas Oliphant.
</P>
<P>
   LANGUAGE-COLUMN (Undated) -- Those pesky little tails that form
our phrasal verbs _ help out, back up, roll over _ can cause no end
of trouble. By Jan Freeman. 800 words.
</P>
