<P>
   Another key to VOXXY, say the women behind it, is that the
concept of girl empowerment spreads across racial and economic
lines in terms of programming content.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have characters of all sizes,'' Kaylor says. ``We have
black, Asian and Latino characters. It's not just your white,
middle-class girls. We're really trying to reach every girl
possible to make it a home and a community.''
</P>
<P>
   So that's what VOXXY is, but how will the high-tech network
work?
</P>
<P>
   VOXXY will begin as a strictly Web-based production. The
programming, heavy in short video streams, will be best viewed with
a high-speed computer modem.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're building the Web experience for high-end users,'' says
Dewey Reid, creative director at Red Sky Interactive, the computer
software and network company that's creating VOXXY'S layout. But he
says that people with slower modems will still be able to enjoy
VOXXY's content _ they'll just miss out on some of the video
streams.
</P>
<P>
   Those with at least a 56K modem will have a good viewing
experience, while people with a Digital Subscriber Line (DSL) _ a
faster Internet connection _ will have a better one. (For the
high-tech challenged: DSL uses existing two-wire copper telephone
wiring and in most cases doesn't require an additional phone line.
It is available through Southwestern Bell, GTE, Charter
Communications, Internet America and AT&AMP;T.)
</P>
<P>
   Currently, AT&AMP;T is working to complete VOXXY's boxes, which are
to be set on top a TV; they should be available at the end of this
year or the beginning of 2001. Once construction of the set-top
boxes is finished, VOXXY will blossom into a dual experience,
combining Internet and television elements.
</P>
<P>
   VOXXY viewers will be able to attach keyboards to their
television, watch VOXXY's programming and log onto the Internet
from the same location. Those who don't have the set-top boxes will
simply use the television and Internet separately.
</P>
<P>
   Will VOXXY change the world with its grrrl empowerment message?
Probably not. But if the plans live up to expectations, the network
looks like a strong step in the direction of quality entertainment
for young women.
</P>
<P>
   ``VOXXY is a new generation of `Web TV,''' Kaylor says. ``We're
taking it a step beyond with unique ways for girls to empower
themselves. We came together to give girls a voice.''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
