<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-14 17:14 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6622 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l BC-CABLENET-SITES-TEX     03-14 0495
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CABLENET-SITES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOUR FUN SITES FOR TEENS
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies CABLE NET-TEENS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   VOXXY isn't set to debut until late spring, so where can teens
find up-to-date, interactive Web sites in the meantime? Try these
four fun, hip Web sites that offer a mixture of news, entertainment
and games. Some are more lighthearted, while others feature
high-brow topics. All are easy to navigate.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   www.chickclick.com
</P>
<P>
   This is an ultracool site that features free e-mail and home
pages. If you want celeb gossip and horoscopes, then this is your
site. On the flip side of the coin, ``chickclick'' presents hard
news including election coverage and forums with questions like,
``Does it matter if there's a Republican or a Democrat in the White
House?'' Other topics include business, health and technology.
Message boards allow teens to interact with other ``chickclick''
users. Bold graphics coupled with current issues make this a highly
entertaining site.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   www.bolt.com
</P>
<P>
   Bolt is geared toward guys and girls. It features many of the
same services as ``chickclick'', but teens have to sign up in order
to use them. ``Bolt.com'' posts daily polls with questions like,
``Who should pay for the prom ticket, the boy or girl?'' The site's
news section presents current events, sports and entertainment.
Dating advice is also available as well as chat boards. Teens can
scan their photo and create a short bio in order to meet other
``bolt.com'' users.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   www.kiwibox.com
</P>
<P>
   Kiwibox is hip without being gaudy. The graphics are totally
low-key, as is its tone. Daily polls are presented, as well as
dating tips and love advice. Membership is also required to use its
boards and to enter contests. In addition, ``kiwibox.com'' features
a word of the day, quote of the day and joke of the day. It even
recognizes and posts the birthdays of its members. The site offers
a mix of lighthearted entertainment along with heavy-hitting
issues, like dealing with divorce. Literary works by teens
nationwide are available for viewing. Titles like, ``We've Come a
Long Way: Life for Women in Shakespeare's Time'' and ``The Prom:
Really That Important?'' will have older teens and young adults
flocking to this site.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   www.accessstyle.com
</P>
<P>
   Fashion is the main theme of ``accessstyle.com/. Ordering
fashion straight from the pages of ``Jump'', ``Seventeen'',
``Teen'' and ``Twist'' is just a click away. Sophie, the site's
animated host, guides you in choosing coordinating pieces and
picking the right lip color. She answers fashion questions and
gives her opinion on the latest trends. Sophie's latest fashion
prediction: snakeskin and feathers will be searing-hot this summer.
Shopaholics and fashion junkies should bookmark this site without
delay.
</P>
<P>
   _ Javonna May-Mons
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
