Evening Sun, as well as to cutbacks in staff and news space at The
Los Angeles Times.
 &HT;    ``I'd been looking at all these things, and I'd been saying, I'm
not going to criticize,'' Chandler said. ``We had just gone out and
hired this wonderful new CEO, and he's seen fit to hire a woman
