<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
timeshold clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, March
15. If you have nyt bcv ubxtic-z  
POLAND (Florence, Ariz.) - Patrick Poland makes his appeal for a
life sentence to the Arizona Board of Executive Clemency. Poland, a
convicted double murderer, is scheduled to die by lethal injection
on Wednesday. The Board is his only hope of a reprieve or a
commutation, but neither is likely. By JUDITH VILLA. Story will
move in the `A` category. 
 
ROBB-COLUMN (Phoenix) - George W. Bush's best hope to become
president is to chart his own course. And, let John McCain decide
for himself the extent to which he wants to play the spoiler. By
ROBERT ROBB. Story will move in the ``K'' category.  
EDIT-MCCAIN (Phoenix) - If later accounts are accurate, MSNBC and
Maria Shriver should be ashamed for having run that nasty little
snippet of film about Sen. John McCain time and again without ever
once revealing the boorishness that precipitated it. Story will
move in the ``K'' category. 
 
MOODY - Ricky Moody, author of `The Ice Storm,` writes joyfylly
about bleak subjects - like drool, death and Richard Nixon. What
makes him so joyous? By BARBARA YOST. Story will move in the ``E''
category. 
 
KUNZ - When Phoenix attorney Don Kunz was a boy, `National
Geographic` transported him to ancient Egypt. He dreamed of one day
visiting the great pyramids and the tombs of the pharaohs, but only
as a tourist. Instead, he was lucky enough to go as an amateur
archeologist and helped to rediscover the greatest tomb since King
Tut's. By BARBARA YOST. Story will move in the ``L'' category. 
 
