POLAND (Florence, Ariz.) - Patrick Poland makes his appeal for a
life sentence to the Arizona Board of Executive Clemency. Poland, a
convicted double murderer, is scheduled to die by lethal injection
on Wednesday. The Board is his only hope of a reprieve or a
commutation, but neither is likely. By JUDITH VILLA. Story will
move in the `A` category. 
 
ROBB-COLUMN (Phoenix) - George W. Bush's best hope to become
