 (Updates by adding information on a grace period for current
clients needing extra time to adjust to the new format.)  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The  &UR; New York Times News Service &LR;  is planning an expanded
weather package, with a planned starting date of Monday, March 20,
to be transmitted Sunday, March 19. The package, consisting of a
weather map as a graphics file and a text file to accompany the
map, is available to graphics clients of the News Service.
</P>
<P>
   The new map grows to 4 columns in width (52 picas), from 3, and
is 6 inches deep; the old was 4\ inches deep. This new size permits
the insertion of cloud cover information, previously a separate
map, and the addition of many new cities (see list below).
</P>
<P>
   The map is available both in color and in black and white.
Because the map is much more detailed, we have devised an entirely
new palette of colors to make it easier to read the added
information.
</P>
<P>
   A sample of the new map is available at Wieck, Newscom,
Presslink and AP's GraphicsNet.
</P>
<P>
   Some papers using the old map may need extra time to make the
transition to a 4-column format. We will, for a limited time,
produce a 3-col version of the new map, but with only some of the
new map's additional cities.
</P>
<P>
   A summary of this information is included in each day's Graphics
Budget.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions, contact
</P>
<P>
   Sergio Florez
</P>
<P>
   Deputy Director for Photos and Graphics New York Times News
Service
</P>
<P>
   Phone: (212) 556-4204
</P>
<P>
   FAX: (212) 556-3535
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: florez(at)nytimes.com
</P>
<P>
   For sales questions, contact
</P>
