<DOCNO> NYT20000314.0231 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-14 18:30 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6684 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u a BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      03-14 0459
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release WEDNESDAY AMs, March 15, 2000  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta
 &LR; at the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of
graphics or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Boston) _ On a day funerals began for 84 army
soldiers killed in an ambush in Chechnya, Russia's former prime
minister says Russia should get out of Chechnya. By Charles Radin.
500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SOUTHERN-PRIMARIES (Plant City, Fla.) _ The southern primaries
have been transformed into a dry run for the the two general
election candidates, both men of the south. This is not territory
that George W. Bush can take for granted; nor can Al Gore. By Anne
E. Kornblut. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPUS-BINGE (Undated) _ Efforts to curb campus binge drinking
aren't working. The percentage of students going on binges stayed
roughly the same through the 1990s, and the percentage of frequent
bingers actually increased, researchers say. By Karen Hsu. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   TREATING-ANEURYSMS (Undated) _ Aneurysms of the abdominal aorta,
a relatively common problem, especially in older people, can now be
treated without major surgery by inserting a graft through a groin
vein with a catheter. The graft is guided into place and expanded.
By Richard Saltus. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   SKAKEL-ARRAIGNMENT (Stamford, Conn.) _ Kennedy nephew Michael
Skakel speaks to Martha Moxley's mother for the first time in
nearly 25 years, telling her on his way out of court: ``I feel your
pain, but you've got the wrong guy.'' By Brian MacQuarrie. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GENOME-SHARING (Undated) _ Shares in biotechnology companies
fall after the United States and Britain agree to share data from a
groundbreaking project to decode the human gene. By Ronald
Rosenberg. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   FIDELITY-BACKLOGS (Boston) _ Fidelity is bogged down in phone
and Web service jams as customers more than double their trading
from a year ago. Other online brokers are struggling with high
volume, too. By Beth Healy. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX-PERFECT (Fort Myers, Fla.) _ Cooperstown has yet to
call, but six Red Sox pitchers accomplish a feat that -- spring
training or no spring training -- is still remarkable. Twenty-seven
Blue Jays went up to the plate, facing Pedro Martinez at the start
and Rod Beck at the end, and 27 Blue Jays were retired. By Michael
Madden. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-14-00 1830EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
