   (NYT19) HOUSTON -- March 14, 2000 -- ELN-RDP -- A polling
station inside the Landmark Furniture store did not see many voters
Tuesday. By late afternoon some four voters had shown up according
to the GOP precinct judge. Al Gore and George W. Bush were
virtually uncontested on Tuesday in six Southern and border state
primaries, the vice president and the Texas governor both certain
to win the delegates to put them close to a nominating majority.
(Phillippe Diederich/The New York Times)
