published by Steerforth Press. Harper's book reveals new details
about the life of Minik, an Eskimo boy brought to New York by
Arctic explorer Robert E. Peary in 1897 and who was unsuccessful in
retrieving his father's remains from the Museum of Natural History
who kept the remains for research after his death. (Steerforth
Press/The New York Times) *LITE
