despite double-checking the fine print for any previously
undisclosed fees, the mortage company First Alliance added $13,000
in fees to her loan which was designed to rise a full percentage
point every six months. The Gundersons, who had to work extra hours
to make ends meet, are among scores of consumers who have
complained to state regulators about First Alliance, a national
home-equity lender based in Irvine, Calif. First Alliance denies
any wrongdoing. (Mitchell Witchell/The New York Times) *LITE
