necessary underpinning, more appreciated in France than in America.
But now, chefs in New York and elsewhere are showcasing shallots,
roasting, glazing, and caramelizing them whole and using them to
garnish salads, vegetables, meat, fish and poultry. (Barbara
Alper/The New York Times)
