<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, MARCH 15
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MRSCLINTON-FUNDRAISING-NYT (moved on Monday, March 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, March 13,
about a fund-raising dinner for Hillary Rodham Clinton by
Pakistani-Americans who hoped to influence President Clinton's
decision on a possible visit to Pakistan misattributed the first
press report of the event. It came from The Staten Island Advance,
not from newspapers in India.
</P>
<P>
   BC-TRIBUNE-NEWMEDIA-NYT (moved on Monday, March 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, March 13,
about the old- and new-media strategies of the Tribune Co. referred
incorrectly to Esther Dyson, a technology newsletter publisher who
said she was unimpressed by the company's merger with Times Mirror.
She has no middle initial.
</P>
<P>
   BC-VIOLENCE-WORKPLACE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Feb. 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Feb. 29,
about changing attitudes in the workplace toward victims of
domestic violence misstated the length of time that Brooke
McMurray, a vice chairwoman of Victim Services in Manhattan, was in
an abusive relationship. It was 6 years, not 12.
</P>
</TEXT>
